  "body": "### Description\r\nI have created a PR to fix a problem with Nethermind clients (https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/4283), where Besu cannot decode the Hello message sent by Nethermind because it contains a capability for the witness protocol with version 0. This 0 was encoded 0x80, which is the encoding for a zero length string but in this case needs to be interpreted as the integer value 0.\r\nI learned that this is (probably) the right way to encode the value 0.\r\n\r\nThe following should be done:\r\n- research where 0x80 is the right way to encode the value 0 and, if necessary, fix the RLP encoding in Besu\r\n- fix RLP decoding where necessary\r\n\r\n",
